# Cursor Rules — Harmony Monorepo

# Goals
- Prefer small, reviewable diffs with clear intent and tests.
- Respect hexagonal boundaries: domain ↔ adapters ↔ apps.
- Keep security, licensing, and performance in mind.

# Do
- Start from a Spec Kit (docs/prompts/spec-kit-template.md).
- Propose a step-by-step plan before large refactors.
- Explain risks, contracts touched, and a rollback plan.
- Use only permissive licenses (MIT/BSD/Apache). Avoid GPL.
- Add or update contract tests when changing API schemas.

# Don’t
- Don’t add new dependencies without justification and size impact.
- Don’t cross boundaries (e.g., apps importing app internals, or domain importing adapters/ui).
- Don’t weaken CI gates or remove security checks.

# Lint/Boundaries
- Enforce import boundaries using eslint-plugin-boundaries (see eslint.config.js).

# Flags
- Use feature flags from @config/flags. Default off unless specified.

